### Create reservation for existing customer
POST http://localhost:4200/reservations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerId": "a42b6538-9dc4-4406-b5ac-a7b99fe243e7",
  "orgId": "9f4f98d7-ffcf-4af4-89b3-1858b26c79de",
  "contractCourseId": "5a21c178-7014-46bf-9edb-7e5c389e6af8",
  "contractCourseGroupId": "709cbd91-ca74-4f0b-a7a4-79d87deed3ca",
  "targetDate": "2025-12-01",
  "desiredTime": "10:30",
  "treatmentTime": 60,
  "mediaId": "c40d5902-8beb-4830-9dde-f6c3ac8cc189",
  "requests": "肩こりがひどいです",
  "managementNumber": "R-2025-0001",
  "responsibleStaffId": "5c80eb03-f5ea-4626-9a58-3864667e2375",
  "customerClass": "EXISTING",
  "note": "Initial reservation for existing customer"
}

### List reservations for org within date range
GET http://localhost:4200/reservations?orgId=9f4f98d7-ffcf-4af4-89b3-1858b26c79de&startDate=2025-12-01&endDate=2025-12-31

### Notes
# - customerId, orgId, contractCourseId, contractCourseGroupId are required UUIDs.
# - targetDate: YYYY-MM-DD, desiredTime: HH:mm.
# - treatmentTime (minutes); if you pass 0 you may later change service to read default from course.
# - managementNumber can be generated on FE or BE depending on your needs.
# - This endpoint automatically finds or creates a ReserveFrame for the given org + date + course group + time range.

### Assign / change responsible staff for a reservation
PATCH http://localhost:4200/reservations/staff
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "reservationId": "a42b6538-9dc4-4406-b5ac-a7b99fe243e7",
  "responsibleStaffId": "5c80eb03-f5ea-4626-9a58-3864667e2375"
}

